Brendan found his grandfather Jack Slade's World War II medals in the Northern Territory . 
  Brendan Cordina drove for four days to the Darwin Military Museum . 
  He was refused the medals and told they were 'more important to the museum' Captain Slade was a flight lieutenant in the war and passed away when Mr Cordina was 12 . 
  The donor of the medals was his wife Mel Slade . 
  The museum director said he respected the intent of the donor . 
 